*formula_5 is the amplitude of the particle displacement;
*formula_6 is the phase shift of the particle displacement;
*formula_7 is the angular wavevector;
*formula_8 is the angular frequency.

It follows that the particle velocity and the sound pressure along the direction of propagation of the sound wave &quot;x&quot; are given by
:formula_9
:formula_10
where
*formula_11 is the amplitude of the particle velocity;
*formula_12 is the phase shift of the particle velocity;
*formula_13 is the amplitude of the acoustic pressure;
*formula_14 is the phase shift of the acoustic pressure.

Taking the Laplace transforms of formula_15 and formula_16 with respect to time yields
:formula_17
